font-weight-regular:   400
```

### Semantic Color Usage
| Context | Token | Hex |
|---------|-------|-----|
| Page background | neutral-90 | #0f0f10 |
| Card / surface | neutral-80 | #171719 |
| Divider / border | neutral-70 | #292a2d |
| Disabled / muted text | neutral-40 | #989ba2 |
| Body text | neutral-10 | #ffffff |
| Primary action / link | primary-40 | #359efa |
| Positive / up trend | secondary-40 | #7de12f |
| Negative / down trend | error-50 | #ff5252 |

## Streamlit Coding Rules

1. **CSS injection** — inject design tokens as CSS variables once at app startup:
   ```python
   st.markdown("""
   <style>
   :root {
     --color-primary-40: #359efa;
     /* ... */
   }
   </style>
   """, unsafe_allow_html=True)
   ```

2. **Caching** — always use `@st.cache_data(ttl=...)` for Snowflake queries.

3. **Session** — use `get_session()` from `vitality_app.session`. Never create a new session.

4. **Tab structure** — each tab is a module with a single `render(...)` function. Don't add logic to `streamlit_app.py`.

5. **State passing** — use dataclasses (like `SidebarState`) to pass state between components. Don't use `st.session_state` for derived data.

6. **Language** — UI labels and messages in Korean. Code (variables, functions, comments) in English.

7. **Charts** — use Altair for statistical charts, Pydeck for maps. Match chart colors to design tokens.

8. **No magic numbers** — reference design token names in comments when using hex colors in Python.

## File Structure
```
I47AIC5MZ97CF0P5/
├── streamlit_app.py         # Entry point only — no business logic here
├── .streamlit/config.toml   # Theme configuration
├── vitality_app/
│   ├── data.py              # Snowflake queries (cached)
│   ├── indices.py           # Index computation
│   ├── session.py           # Snowflake session singleton
│   ├── sidebar.py           # Sidebar UI
│   └── tabs/                # One module per tab
```
